      <Abstract xml:lang="en">Companies use different strategies to construct organizational legitimacy and overcome information asymmetry. However, they often rely on traditional media, such as annual report disclosure or press releases, to construct organizational legitimacy. In contrast, external stakeholders start to contribute to organizational legitimacy via mass self-communication. For example, consumers use online social network sites for collaborative interaction through the production of product reviews via YouTube, the verification of information via blogs, Facebook groups and Wikis, and the discussion of organizational topics through blogs, Facebook and Twitter. The aim of the study is to contribute to the development of theory on organizational legitimacy by analysing the influence of mass self-communication on the construction of organizational legitimacy in the German natural cosmetic industry.</Abstract>
